REASONING: The Land Transport Authority (official) page shows line colour assignments and station codes; it lists the East-West Line as Green and identifies Chinatown station as NE4/DT19 (North East Line / Downtown Line) — i.e. not East-West (Green). Snippet: "SMRT operates ... East-West Line (Green)" and "Chinatown MRT Station (NE4/DT19) is located on the North East Line and Downtown Line."

The operator SBSTransit station information page for Chinatown lists the station under the North East Line (purple) and the Downtown Line (blue). Snippet: "Train Line: Downtown Line Blue  North East Line Purple" and Chinatown is shown as a station on those lines.

Because Chinatown MRT (Singapore) is on the North East Line (purple) and the Downtown Line (blue), and the Green line refers to the East-West Line, the claim "Chinatown MRT is on the green line" is incorrect.
